# Open Graph Image - Required for Every Page

**When adding a new page with metadata, ALWAYS add `opengraph-image.tsx`** in the same route folder. Use the dynamic SVG-based image via `StaticOgImage`, never static PNG URLs.

## Pattern

For each new page/route (e.g. `app/my-page/`), create:

```
app/my-page/
  layout.tsx      # metadata with openGraph/twitter
  opengraph-image.tsx   # REQUIRED - dynamic OG image
  page.tsx
```

## opengraph-image.tsx Template

```tsx
import { ImageResponse } from "next/og"
import { StaticOgImage, OG_IMAGE_WIDTH, OG_IMAGE_HEIGHT } from "@/components/og/StaticOgImage"

export const alt = "Page Title - SoundButtons.com"
export const size = { width: OG_IMAGE_WIDTH, height: OG_IMAGE_HEIGHT }
export const contentType = "image/png"

export default function OgImage() {
  return new ImageResponse(
    <StaticOgImage title="Page Title" subtitle="Optional Subtitle" />,
    { ...size }
  )
}
```

## Layout

- Do NOT add explicit `images` to openGraph or twitter in layout metadata
- Next.js will auto-use the route's `opengraph-image.tsx`
- Add comment: `// Uses opengraph-image.tsx for dynamic OG image`
